                    </article>

                                                                                                </div>
                        

                        <p>It was a sober experience, but not an overwhelming one. I didn't burst into tears at 4:31. My body didn't shudder.</p>
<p>I simply caught my breath and paused to reflect.</p>
<p>As I left the sidewalk gathering, I spotted a bright, full moon in one corner of the sky. In another corner a star blazed like a diamond. Together they lit the sky, even before the sun's warm came shining through.</p>
<p>I was ready to start the new year.</p>
<p>Jason Greenwald, Trinity '93, is a former editor of The Chronicle and currently lives in Los Angeles.</p>
